# Files EAS Build should EXCLUDE from the upload. When present, this file
# fully replaces the .gitignore-based defaults for the build tarball — so we
# must list everything we still want excluded (node_modules, native builds,
# secrets that DON'T belong in a build), and NOT list files EAS needs at
# build time even though they're gitignored.
#
# Notably, `.env` is intentionally NOT listed here: `app.config.js` reads
# EAS_PROJECT_ID and EAS_OWNER from process.env during EAS's build phase; if
# .env isn't uploaded, those come out undefined and push registration fails
# on device with "No projectId found." Ditto google-services.json for FCM.

node_modules
android
ios
.expo
.expo-shared
web-build
dist
build
coverage
*.log

# OS / editor cruft
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.vscode
.idea

# Signing artifacts / provisioning that should NEVER go into a build tarball.
*.jks
*.keystore
*.p8
*.p12
*.key
*.mobileprovision

# FCM V1 service account key is uploaded to Expo, NEVER embedded in the app.
credentials/google-service-account-key.json
